1
00:00:04,136 --> 00:00:06,986
Once, in the Bṛhad-bhāgavatāmṛta,

2
00:00:06,986 --> 00:00:10,602
when Gopa Kumār’s praising Śiva

3
00:00:11,509 --> 00:00:12,813
as the greatest devotee,

4
00:00:12,813 --> 00:00:15,903
vaiṣṇavānāṁ yathā Śambhuḥ,

5
00:00:15,903 --> 00:00:19,410
and Śiva is trying to deflect 
this praise, he said,

6
00:00:19,410 --> 00:00:22,944
“I am so shameful!”

7
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:25,882
[Greater than God]

8
00:00:26,689 --> 00:00:28,097
“What?”

9
00:00:28,097 --> 00:00:31,843
“I preached this Māyāvād philosophy 
of Śaṇkar.

10
00:00:31,843 --> 00:00:35,337
Not only that;
actually, I once expressed

11
00:00:35,337 --> 00:00:39,294
that I wanted to be greater
than the Lord,

12
00:00:39,294 --> 00:00:44,324
greater than Kṛṣṇa.
I’m so shameless!” 

13
00:00:45,308 --> 00:00:50,001
And then Sanātan Goswāmī 
explains in his purport, saying,

14
00:00:50,539 --> 00:00:53,788
“Don’t take Śiva’s words
at face value.

15
00:00:53,788 --> 00:00:57,172
What is he really saying?

16
00:00:57,465 --> 00:01:01,292
He’s speaking in
a self-deprecating way by saying,

17
00:01:01,292 --> 00:01:05,364
“I wanted a position 
greater than Kṛṣṇa!”

18
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:08,010
And Sanātan Goswāmī explains,

19
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:12,777
“What is that position?
Devotee.”

20
00:01:13,499 --> 00:01:16,838
The devotees are taken 
to be greater than Kṛṣṇa, 

21
00:01:16,838 --> 00:01:20,179
so he's saying,
“I want to be your devotee”,

22
00:01:20,179 --> 00:01:21,786
But he is saying this
as if it was a fault:

23
00:01:21,786 --> 00:01:24,749
“I wanted a position 
greater than the Lord,

24
00:01:24,749 --> 00:01:28,367
that’s the kind of
despicable man I am!”

25
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:31,504
So beautifully expressed there.

